1
00:00:03,629 --> 00:00:08,258
TASHA LEM: Once there was a planet,
much like any other

2
00:00:08,675 --> 00:00:10,052
and unimportant.

3
00:00:11,428 --> 00:00:13,764
This planet sent the universe
a message,

4
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:17,726
a bell tolling among the stars,

5
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:21,647
ringing out to all
the dark corners of creation.

6
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:24,274
And everybody came to see.

7
00:00:26,485 --> 00:00:29,112
Although no one understood the message,

8
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:32,824
everyone who heard it
found themselves afraid,

9
00:00:33,742 --> 00:00:35,786
except one man,

10
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:38,372
the man who stayed for Christmas.

11
00:00:40,666 --> 00:00:44,878
I bring proof of courage
and comradeship.

12
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:47,756
What is this ship and why are you here?

13
00:00:49,675 --> 00:00:53,679
Identify yourselves by species
and planet of origin.

14
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:58,225
(SONIC BEEPING)

15
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:03,188
Exterminate!

16
00:01:03,814 --> 00:01:05,607
-Exterminate!
-Handles?

17
00:01:05,732 --> 00:01:08,110
-Exterminate!
-Handles, wrong ship.

18
00:01:08,193 --> 00:01:11,822
-Exterminate!
-Ah! Handles, it's wrong. Handles!

19
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:13,574
Exterminate!

20
00:01:14,157 --> 00:01:15,909
Every ship I go on,
they just shoot at me.

21
00:01:15,993 --> 00:01:19,454
Handles, I said put me on a ship.
I didn't say put me on a Dalek ship.

22
00:01:19,538 --> 00:01:23,417
Don't put me on a Dalek ship
when I'm holding a broken bit of Dalek!

23
00:01:23,792 --> 00:01:25,460
Ow!

24
00:01:25,544 --> 00:01:27,838
-You did not indicate a preference.
-Use your head!

25
00:01:27,921 --> 00:01:30,632
It's not like you've got a lot
of alternatives. They're all here.

26
00:01:30,716 --> 00:01:32,926
Daleks, Sontarans,
Terileptils, Slitheen,

27
00:01:33,010 --> 00:01:36,179
and they're not even fighting,
they're just parked. Why?

28
00:01:36,263 --> 00:01:38,348
The message was received
throughout the universe.

29
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:42,185
Yes, yes, the message, the message.
Even I can't translate it.

30
00:01:43,604 --> 00:01:46,106
Why is everyone here
if they don't understand it?

31
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:47,316
You're here.

32
00:01:47,399 --> 00:01:49,943
Well, you know.
I'm OCD, what's their excuse?

33
00:01:50,027 --> 00:01:51,737
What does this message mean?

34
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:53,363
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

35
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:55,365
Oh, no! And remind me,

36
00:01:55,449 --> 00:01:57,951
I've got to patch the telephone
back through the console unit,

37
00:01:58,035 --> 00:01:59,161
this is getting ridiculous.

38
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:02,122
-Attention! Information available.
-Okay.

39
00:02:02,873 --> 00:02:05,959
You must patch the telephone device
back through the console unit.

40
00:02:06,043 --> 00:02:08,420
No, no, no, no, no, not now!
Remind me later.

41
00:02:09,004 --> 00:02:10,339
-When?
-I don't know, just later,

42
00:02:10,422 --> 00:02:11,840
-just pick a time.
-When?

43
00:02:11,923 --> 00:02:14,551
I don't know, just any old time,
just when you think I've forgotten.

44
00:02:14,635 --> 00:02:16,261
-When?
-Just pick a random number,

45
00:02:16,345 --> 00:02:18,055
express that number
as a quantity of minutes

46
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,348
and when that time has elapsed,

47
00:02:19,431 --> 00:02:22,851
remind me to patch the telephone
back through the console unit.

48
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:23,977
Affirmative.

49
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:26,396
-(TELEPHONE RINGING)
-How those Cyber-evenings must fly.

50
00:02:29,024 --> 00:02:33,236
-Hello, the Tardis.
-Emergency. You're my boyfriend.

51
00:02:33,487 --> 00:02:34,988
Ding-dong! Okay, brilliant.

52
00:02:35,072 --> 00:02:39,409
I may be a bit rusty in some areas
but I will glance at a manual.

53
00:02:39,826 --> 00:02:42,371
No, no, you're not actually
my boyfriend.

54
00:02:42,454 --> 00:02:45,082
Well, that was quick.
It's a roller coaster, this phone call.

55
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:47,167
But I need a boyfriend really quickly.

56
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:48,919
Well, I hope you're nicer
to the next one.

57
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:51,630
No, shut up! Christmas dinner,

58
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:53,882
-me cooking.
-So?

59
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:58,553
So I may have accidentally
invented a boyfriend.

60
00:02:58,637 --> 00:03:01,473
Yeah, I did that once. And there's
no easy way to get rid of an android.

61
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:04,976
No, not an android, a pretend one,
an imaginary one,

62
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:07,145
and I said he'd be coming
to Christmas dinner.

63
00:03:07,229 --> 00:03:08,563
Yeah.

64
00:03:08,647 --> 00:03:11,858
Handles, that's a new ship.
Okay, we'll take the Tardis this time.

65
00:03:11,942 --> 00:03:14,027
I just need you to come for
Christmas dinner, just do that for me.

66
00:03:14,111 --> 00:03:16,988
Just come to Christmas dinner
and be my Christmas date.

67
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:20,701
Sorry, missed that last bit.
Got to dash!

68
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:30,168
Okay, don't be alarmed, I come in...

69
00:03:33,672 --> 00:03:34,881
Alert alert!

70
00:03:34,965 --> 00:03:36,007
Peace. No!

71
00:03:36,091 --> 00:03:37,426
Intruder detected.

72
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:40,220
The intruder will be upgraded.

73
00:03:40,762 --> 00:03:42,431
(DOCTOR EXCLAIMING)

74
00:03:42,556 --> 00:03:43,598
Sorry!

75
00:03:44,808 --> 00:03:46,518
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

76
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:51,314
I need you.
I'm cooking Christmas dinner!

77
00:03:51,398 --> 00:03:54,317
-I'm being shot at by Cybermen!
-Well, can't we do both?

78
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:55,527
Ohh... Yeah, why not?

79
00:03:56,778 --> 00:03:59,197
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

80
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,482
PRESENTERS: Happy Christmas!

81
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:37,611
-How's the turkey doing?
-Great, yeah, yeah, it's doing great.

82
00:04:37,861 --> 00:04:41,448
Well, dead and decapitated, but that's
Christmas when you're a turkey.

83
00:04:43,366 --> 00:04:46,203
Actually, maybe I will have
a little more.

84
00:04:46,828 --> 00:04:49,831
-There you go, Gran.
-Did you put it in early enough?

85
00:04:49,915 --> 00:04:51,333
Dad, I put it in when you phoned me.

86
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:54,711
-I emailed you some instructions.
-Oh, you certainly did.

87
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:57,589
(WHOOSHING)

88
00:05:09,184 --> 00:05:10,560
Doctor, I so need you...

89
00:05:12,062 --> 00:05:13,230
Clara!

90
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:17,776
No, stop. Stop, don't move.
Don't do anything.

91
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:20,904
-Why, what is it? What's wrong?
-You're naked.

92
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:24,741
Yes, I am naked.
I wondered if you'd notice.

93
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:28,662
-Doctor, why are you naked?
-Because I'm going to church.

94
00:05:34,376 --> 00:05:37,420
-Better?
-Oh, that was quick.

95
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:40,340
Hologram clothes, projected directly
onto your visual cortex.

96
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:42,926
-So you're still naked underneath?
-Everybody's naked underneath.

97
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:44,886
Ugh! Don't say things like that,
it's Christmas.

98
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:46,346
Come meet my family.

99
00:05:46,763 --> 00:05:49,850
Hello! So, er, here he is!

100
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:52,978
Hello, the Oswalds! Hello!

101
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:56,439
Merry Christmas. Hello, hello!

102
00:05:57,899 --> 00:05:59,317
Hello, handsome.

103
00:06:01,528 --> 00:06:02,863
Anyone for Twister?

104
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:06,032
So, this is the Doctor, my boyfriend.

105
00:06:06,116 --> 00:06:07,284
(GRAN GIGGLES)

106
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,786
CLARA: Isn't anybody going to say hello?

107
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:13,748
Hello. (GIGGLES)

108
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,294
Excuse me a moment.

109
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:19,629
Listen, I've got an idea
to break the ice.

110
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:22,549
Why don't I project my clothes hologram
onto their visual cortexes, too?

111
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:25,176
So, to be clear, no one except me
can see your clothes?

112
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:27,929
Yes, and I'm starting to think
it may be causing tension.

113
00:06:28,013 --> 00:06:30,181
Are we playing Twister now?

114
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:32,934
-Get in the kitchen!
-Hey? Sorry!

115
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:37,772
Sorry, he's Swedish.

116
00:06:41,902 --> 00:06:43,445
Doctor, please!

117
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:45,989
Oh, that's never going to work, is it?

118
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:47,991
What's wrong?
Do you not think it's done yet?

119
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:49,993
I think a decent vet would
give it an even chance.

120
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:51,828
-Okay, well, use an app.
-An app?

121
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:53,204
On your screwdriver, app it.

122
00:06:53,288 --> 00:06:55,123
Most certainly not,
it doesn't do turkey.

123
00:06:55,415 --> 00:06:58,501
Nothing does turkey,
you'd need a time machine.

124
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:03,757
What?

125
00:07:05,592 --> 00:07:07,344
You can't keep using
the Tardis like this.

126
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:08,470
Like what?

127
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:10,388
Missed birthdays, restaurant bookings.

128
00:07:10,472 --> 00:07:14,100
And please, just learn
how to use iPlayer.

129
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:17,020
Ooh, vortex cooking?

130
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:20,732
Yep, exposure to the time winds.
It'll either come up a treat

131
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:22,651
or just possibly lay some eggs.

132
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:25,487
-CYBERHEAD: Information available.
-What's that?

133
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:28,782
Just a bit of a Cyberman.
He'll get us to the church on time.

134
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:30,200
I have developed a fault.

135
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:33,787
The organics are all gone but there's
still a full set of data banks.

136
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:35,664
Found it at the Maldovar market.

137
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:40,418
Planet identified
from analysis of message.

138
00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:44,673
Right, cool. Go on, then, okay, tell us.
What is the planet? Go on.

139
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:47,300
Processing official designation.

140
00:07:48,927 --> 00:07:50,011
Processing.

141
00:07:50,095 --> 00:07:52,138
Okay, in your own time, dear,
don't rush.

142
00:07:54,015 --> 00:07:56,226
So why haven't you just gone down there,
had a look?

143
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:58,687
It's shielded.
Even the Tardis can't break through it.

144
00:07:59,437 --> 00:08:00,605
Gallifrey.

145
00:08:05,527 --> 00:08:06,820
What did you say?

146
00:08:12,951 --> 00:08:14,619
Gallifrey.

147
00:08:14,703 --> 00:08:17,455
What are you talking about, Gallifrey?
What do you mean?

148
00:08:17,539 --> 00:08:21,251
Confirmed.
Planet designation, Gallifrey.

149
00:08:23,586 --> 00:08:28,299
You see that? Gallifrey is my home,
I know it when I see it.

150
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:31,177
That is not Gallifrey!

151
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:36,141
-Doctor, are you okay?
-It's not Gallifrey. Gallifrey's gone.

152
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:43,064
Unless... Unless you saved it.
You thought you might have.

153
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:47,777
Even if it survived,
it's gone from this universe.

154
00:08:47,861 --> 00:08:49,154
That is not my home.

155
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:54,242
It can't be.

156
00:08:55,118 --> 00:08:56,911
(SHIP'S HORN BLARING)

157
00:08:57,996 --> 00:08:59,164
What's that?

158
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:09,924
The Papal Mainframe.
It's like a great big flying church.

159
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,260
The first ship to arrive,

160
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:14,012
they're the ones
who shielded the planet,

161
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:15,889
they can get us down there.

162
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:20,018
CLARA: Friend of yours?

163
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:22,812
Tasha Lem, the Mother Superious.

164
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:29,527
-Oh, she's inviting us aboard.
-Why?

165
00:09:29,944 --> 00:09:31,821
Because I asked her. Swallow this.

166
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:33,865
-What is it?
-Your hologram projector.

167
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:36,534
You can't go to church
with your clothes on!

168
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,796
I don't feel like I'm wearing anything.

169
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:51,174
-I know, relaxing, isn't it?
-What is this place?

170
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:54,928
The Church of the Papal Mainframe,
security hub of the known universe.

171
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:56,221
A security church?

172
00:09:56,638 --> 00:10:00,100
Yep, keeping you safe in this world
and the next.

173
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:04,771
I venerate the exaltation
of the Mother Superious.

174
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:09,150
Welcome to the Church
of the Papal Mainframe.

175
00:10:09,234 --> 00:10:10,985
Your nudity is appreciated.

176
00:10:12,695 --> 00:10:13,738
Hey, babes.

177
00:10:13,863 --> 00:10:17,450
-Loving the frock.
-Is that a new body? Give us a twirl!

178
00:10:17,534 --> 00:10:20,453
Tash, this old thing? Please!
I've been rocking it for centuries.

179
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:22,872
Nice, though. Tight.

180
00:10:23,206 --> 00:10:25,542
So, uh, hello! Also here.

181
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:29,504
Clara, this is Tasha Lem, the head
of the Church of the Papal Mainframe.

182
00:10:29,712 --> 00:10:33,049
(LAUGHING) Tash, this is my...

183
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:42,142
My associate, Clara Oswald.
Miss Clara Oswald.

184
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:46,020
We'll go to my chapel.

185
00:10:46,104 --> 00:10:50,775
All honors in place,
no sacrifices required.

186
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:54,696
It was Tasha who shielded the planet.

187
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:57,490
But you could sneak me
down there, couldn't you, Tash?

188
00:10:58,074 --> 00:11:00,326
I would have conditions.

189
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:03,955
I have confidential matters
to discuss with the Doctor.

190
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:06,291
Would you excuse us?

191
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:09,586
Anything you have to say to me
you can say in front of Clara.

192
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:12,505
Well, quite a lot of it.

193
00:11:12,881 --> 00:11:15,175
Probably about half,

194
00:11:15,258 --> 00:11:19,012
maybe a smidge under.

195
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:21,347
Actually, Clara, would you mind
waiting out here, please?

196
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:24,017
No worries.
You two get yourselves a room.

197
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,436
Yes, quite. No, stop it!

198
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:29,063
Boss of the psycho space nuns. So you!

199
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:34,527
DOCTOR: Well...

200
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:39,699
(GASPS)

201
00:11:42,827 --> 00:11:44,287
(RASPING)

202
00:11:46,915 --> 00:11:47,957
Doctor.

203
00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:53,546
-That altar looks like a bed.
-That bed looks like an altar.

204
00:11:54,297 --> 00:11:55,423
Yep.

205
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:05,975
Excuse me.

206
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:13,483
That message is transmitting
through all of space and time.

207
00:12:14,317 --> 00:12:16,110
What did it make you feel?

208
00:12:16,778 --> 00:12:17,820
Feel?

209
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:21,991
Every sentient being in the universe
who detected that signal felt something.

210
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:23,952
Something overpowering.

211
00:12:24,869 --> 00:12:26,955
-What?
-Fear.

212
00:12:28,081 --> 00:12:31,084
Pure, unadulterated dread.

213
00:12:43,513 --> 00:12:45,765
I saw you and then I forgot you,
how does that work?

214
00:12:46,057 --> 00:12:47,392
(RASPING)

215
00:12:54,941 --> 00:12:57,068
Right, what's the signal,
where's it coming from?

216
00:12:57,485 --> 00:13:00,488
It's a settlement.
Human colony, level two.

217
00:13:00,571 --> 00:13:03,616
-A farm, basically.
-Right, anyone been for a look?

218
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:08,162
Any one ship lands, the rest
will follow, there will be bloodshed.

219
00:13:08,997 --> 00:13:13,334
Fortunately, we got here first,
shielded the planet.

220
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:17,130
We maintain the truce
by blocking all of them.

221
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:21,009
Daleks, Cybermen. One of that lot
could break through your defenses.

222
00:13:21,134 --> 00:13:23,428
Perhaps, but they're afraid, remember?

223
00:13:24,137 --> 00:13:25,930
Nobody wants to go first.

224
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:29,851
-I do.
-I was counting on it.

225
00:13:29,934 --> 00:13:31,561
(RASPING) Confess.

226
00:13:34,272 --> 00:13:35,356
(GASPS)

227
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,317
Confess.

228
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,777
What are you?
Why do I keep forgetting you?

229
00:13:41,404 --> 00:13:42,822
Confess.

230
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:45,033
To what?

231
00:13:49,329 --> 00:13:50,371
You okay?

232
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:54,709
Fine. Yeah, fine, sorry.

233
00:13:55,418 --> 00:13:58,755
Right, this is my personal teleport.

234
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:01,507
I can put you down
just outside the town.

235
00:14:01,591 --> 00:14:04,802
Find the source of the message
and report back to me in one hour.

236
00:14:04,886 --> 00:14:08,765
And on your life, Doctor,
you will cause no trouble down there.

237
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:10,933
When do I?

238
00:14:11,017 --> 00:14:12,685
Don't answer that.

239
00:14:15,605 --> 00:14:17,231
-What?
-I'm not an idiot.

240
00:14:17,315 --> 00:14:20,526
Everyone in this church is trained
to see straight through holograms.

241
00:14:20,610 --> 00:14:21,778
Ah, great!

242
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:26,574
Give now. You're taking no
technology of any kind down there.

243
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:29,619
What can I do with a key? You, in, now.

244
00:14:32,038 --> 00:14:33,331
You could summon your Tardis.

245
00:14:33,414 --> 00:14:35,917
The Tardis doesn't work by remote.

246
00:14:36,626 --> 00:14:40,588
Fine, if it makes you feel any better,
there we are.

247
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:46,677
Remember, I want you back in one hour.

248
00:14:52,642 --> 00:14:54,685
-(SHIVERING) Oh, cold, very cold.
-Okay, don't worry.

249
00:14:54,769 --> 00:14:56,813
There's a heat loss filter
in your hologram shell,

250
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:58,398
it'll kick in, just give it a moment.

251
00:14:58,481 --> 00:15:03,736
So, sweet little town covered in snow,
half the universe in terror. Why?

252
00:15:05,238 --> 00:15:06,280
DOCTOR: Why?

253
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:08,783
-Oh, my God!
-What?

254
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:12,620
-Something under the snow, it's...
-What is it?

255
00:15:13,329 --> 00:15:14,539
...cold.

256
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:16,707
Okay, just stand back, please, Clara.

257
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:19,919
It's stone.
It's just stone, it's only a statue.

258
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:24,799
-Clara, step away from it!
-(GASPS)

259
00:15:25,425 --> 00:15:30,263
Clara, keep looking at it,
don't look away! Don't even blink!

260
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:32,265
-What is it?
-There is a Weeping Angel

261
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:33,474
under the snow.

262
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:35,852
It looks like a statue, isn't a statue.
Can you get your foot out?

263
00:15:35,935 --> 00:15:37,228
Only if I can get it out of my shoe.

264
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:38,604
-You're not wearing a shoe.
-Good point.

265
00:15:38,688 --> 00:15:40,815
Okay, just pull, hard!

266
00:15:40,898 --> 00:15:44,652
-I'm trying!
-Go on! One, two, three!

267
00:15:45,361 --> 00:15:46,696
(STRAINING)

268
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:48,573
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

269
00:15:55,455 --> 00:15:56,497
Oh, God!

270
00:15:57,915 --> 00:15:59,292
They're climbing out of the snow.

271
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:01,544
-Oh! Oh, God.
-Keep looking at them, at all of them.

272
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:02,879
Why?

273
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:05,631
Quantum-locked life form,
it can only move if it's unobserved.

274
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:06,841
What are they doing here?

275
00:16:06,924 --> 00:16:09,260
Same as everybody else,
they must have got past Tasha's shield.

276
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:12,889
Ah! Keep looking!

277
00:16:13,473 --> 00:16:16,142
I can't, I can't see,
the snow is in my eyes.

278
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:18,352
Look, I just need to bring
the Tardis down.

279
00:16:18,436 --> 00:16:20,688
-You can't fly it remotely.
-No, but it can hone in on the key.

280
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:24,066
-She took your key!
-She took one of them.

281
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:27,695
(GASPS)

282
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:29,572
Engines activating.

283
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:31,991
(WHOOSHING)

284
00:16:33,743 --> 00:16:35,995
The old key-in-the-quiff routine,
classic!

285
00:16:36,287 --> 00:16:38,956
Okay, homing in
on the mysterious message.

286
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:42,210
Ooh, yes, I like that,
the mysterious message.

287
00:16:42,293 --> 00:16:43,377
You shaved your head?

288
00:16:43,461 --> 00:16:45,713
Yep. Clever plan to get us
past the shield.

289
00:16:45,796 --> 00:16:47,298
You got bored one night, didn't you?

290
00:16:47,632 --> 00:16:49,258
Yeah, tiny bit bored.

291
00:16:49,342 --> 00:16:51,135
Is that what happened to your eyebrows?

292
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:53,304
No, they're just delicate.

293
00:16:54,263 --> 00:16:57,642
Right, setting us down
near the signal's source.

294
00:16:57,725 --> 00:17:01,437
I'm going to turn the engines on silent,
don't want to make a fuss.

295
00:17:01,896 --> 00:17:03,397
-Put it back on.
-Why?

296
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:06,526
-Your ears are like rocket fins.
-I know.

297
00:17:11,239 --> 00:17:13,866
Oh, it's good to be wearing
clothes again.

298
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:15,618
That is so much better! Don't you think?

299
00:17:15,701 --> 00:17:18,287
Now, what do we make of this place?

300
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:21,374
It's two o'clock in the afternoon,
must be very short days here.

301
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:24,544
The message is coming from that tower.

302
00:17:26,254 --> 00:17:28,631
Hello! Hello there!

303
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:30,550
Right, we're a couple
from the next town,

304
00:17:30,633 --> 00:17:32,843
my name's probably Hank
or Rock, something like that.

305
00:17:33,302 --> 00:17:34,554
-Or Daisy?
-Shut up.

306
00:17:34,637 --> 00:17:37,848
Hello, good to meet you, nice snow.

307
00:17:37,932 --> 00:17:41,143
-Most pleasant to meet you, too.
-Most pleasant, most pleasant.

308
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:43,521
I'm the Doctor. I'm a Time Lord
from the planet Gallifrey.

309
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:45,481
I stole a time machine and ran away

310
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:49,902
and I've been flouting the principle law
of my own people ever since.

311
00:17:51,112 --> 00:17:52,947
That wasn't quite
what I was meant to say!

312
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,574
I'm an English teacher
from the planet Earth

313
00:17:54,657 --> 00:17:57,368
and I've run off with a man from space
because I really fancy him...

314
00:17:57,451 --> 00:18:01,163
I think perhaps you should
stop talking till you get used to it.

315
00:18:01,372 --> 00:18:02,415
Used to what?

316
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:03,916
What did you say your name was?

317
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,668
Bubbly personality masking
bossy control freak!

318
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:06,836
I'm wearing a wig!

319
00:18:06,961 --> 00:18:08,170
(BOTH LAUGHING)

320
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:12,592
No, ah, I see. Yes, of course.
It's a truth field.

321
00:18:12,842 --> 00:18:15,428
Oh, that is so quaint.
I haven't seen a truth field in years!

322
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:16,596
I'm wearing a wig!

323
00:18:16,679 --> 00:18:18,306
No one can lie in this town.

324
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:21,267
Especially this close to the tower.

325
00:18:23,144 --> 00:18:25,021
Doesn't that make life a bit difficult?

326
00:18:25,146 --> 00:18:26,355
-Not at all.
-Yes.

327
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:30,526
-This town, what's it called?
-It's Christmas.

328
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:32,778
-It's July.
-No, the town.

329
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:35,364
The town is Christmas,
that's what it's called.

330
00:18:35,865 --> 00:18:38,117
Be happy here. Be well!

331
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,952
How can a town be called Christmas?

332
00:18:40,036 --> 00:18:42,204
I don't know,
how can an island be called Easter?

333
00:18:42,330 --> 00:18:45,958
Maybe it's just nice here.
I almost hate to find out what's wrong.

334
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:03,643
There you are.

335
00:19:06,228 --> 00:19:07,563
What took you so long?

336
00:19:08,397 --> 00:19:10,691
What's wrong?
It's only a crack in the wall.

337
00:19:18,949 --> 00:19:23,412
I knew. I always knew it wasn't over.

338
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,542
What is it?

339
00:19:29,752 --> 00:19:31,879
A split in the skin of reality.

340
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:47,603
A tiny sliver of the 26th of June, 2010.

341
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:50,231
-The day the universe blew up.
-Missed that.

342
00:19:50,356 --> 00:19:51,941
I rebooted it,
put it all back together again.

343
00:19:52,066 --> 00:19:53,109
That's good.

344
00:19:53,234 --> 00:19:54,694
Well, it was my Tardis that blew it up
in the first place,

345
00:19:54,777 --> 00:19:58,280
I felt a degree of responsibility.
But the scar tissue remains.

346
00:19:58,406 --> 00:20:01,784
A structural weakness
in the whole universe. Whoa!

347
00:20:02,618 --> 00:20:05,287
And someone's trying to get through it
from outside our universe,

348
00:20:05,413 --> 00:20:08,624
from somewhere else.
Of course, of course! Makes sense.

349
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:10,209
-It does?
-Yes.

350
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:12,545
If you were trying to break through
a wall, you'd choose the weakest spot.

351
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:13,963
If you were trying to break
into this universe,

352
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:15,715
you'd choose this crack because...

353
00:20:15,798 --> 00:20:18,384
No. If you were trying to break back
into this universe.

354
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:21,470
You said Gallifrey.
Why did you say Gallifrey?

355
00:20:22,138 --> 00:20:23,889
Analysis of message composition

356
00:20:23,973 --> 00:20:28,060
indicates Gallifreyan origin,
according to Tardis data banks.

357
00:20:28,144 --> 00:20:29,729
You said Gallifrey was gone.

358
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:33,399
No, I said it was in another universe.

359
00:20:33,482 --> 00:20:35,484
The message is coming through here.

360
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:37,403
The truth field is, too, at a guess.

361
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:40,573
If it's the Time Lords,
if it's the Time Lords...

362
00:20:47,329 --> 00:20:48,831
Seal of the High Council of Gallifrey,

363
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:51,083
nicked it off the Master
in the Death Zone.

364
00:20:51,167 --> 00:20:54,837
There is an algorithm imprinted
in the atomic structure,

365
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,172
use it to decode the message.

366
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:59,633
Message decoding.
Message analysis proceeding.

367
00:21:00,926 --> 00:21:02,762
Information available.

368
00:21:02,845 --> 00:21:05,931
The message is a request
for information.

369
00:21:06,015 --> 00:21:10,311
It's a question.
Why can't you just say it's a question?

370
00:21:10,644 --> 00:21:13,773
It is being projected through
all of time and space

371
00:21:13,856 --> 00:21:15,691
on a repeating cycle.

372
00:21:16,984 --> 00:21:21,530
The oldest question in the universe,
hidden in plain sight...

373
00:21:21,655 --> 00:21:26,368
Warning, translation will be available
to all life-forms in range.

374
00:21:26,619 --> 00:21:27,953
Translation follows.

375
00:21:29,205 --> 00:21:31,040
Doctor who?

376
00:21:31,665 --> 00:21:33,125
Doctor who?

377
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:35,503
THE GENERAL: Doctor who?

378
00:21:36,337 --> 00:21:38,005
Doctor who?

379
00:21:38,881 --> 00:21:40,549
Doctor who?

380
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:43,177
Doctor who?

381
00:21:43,886 --> 00:21:45,554
Doctor who?

382
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:48,474
Doctor who?

383
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:51,227
Doctor who?

384
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:53,729
Doctor who?

385
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:57,399
Patch me through to the Doctor. Now!

386
00:21:58,484 --> 00:22:00,903
A question only I could answer,

387
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:04,990
a truth field to make sure
I'm not lying.

388
00:22:07,076 --> 00:22:09,912
If I give my name, they'll know
they've found the right place

389
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:14,500
and that it's safe to come through.

390
00:22:15,918 --> 00:22:17,002
The Time Lords?

391
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:20,589
Okay, so what then?
If you answer the question

392
00:22:20,714 --> 00:22:23,092
and they come back, what happens?

393
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:25,845
Ah, you need to take this to the Tardis

394
00:22:25,928 --> 00:22:27,596
and put it in the charger slot
for the sonic.

395
00:22:27,763 --> 00:22:28,848
Why?

396
00:22:28,931 --> 00:22:33,435
Hell. All hell, that's what happens
if the Time Lords come back.

397
00:22:33,561 --> 00:22:36,564
There's half the universe up there
already, waiting to open fire.

398
00:22:36,772 --> 00:22:40,860
Now, please, go to the Tardis
and just do as I say!

399
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:49,076
TASHA LEM: Doctor!

400
00:22:50,244 --> 00:22:51,787
Speak with me.

401
00:22:58,794 --> 00:23:02,047
Doctor! Face me now!

402
00:23:07,970 --> 00:23:09,263
Doctor.

403
00:23:12,308 --> 00:23:15,644
Mother Superious, there is only
one thing I need from you.

404
00:23:15,728 --> 00:23:18,898
This planet, what's it called?

405
00:23:20,774 --> 00:23:21,942
Trenzalore.

406
00:23:28,616 --> 00:23:30,993
Okay, is that it?

407
00:23:31,118 --> 00:23:32,494
Are you doing a clever thing?

408
00:23:32,578 --> 00:23:36,415
If you speak your name,
the Time Lords will return.

409
00:23:36,498 --> 00:23:38,500
If they return, they will come in peace.

410
00:23:38,626 --> 00:23:43,422
It doesn't matter, they will be met
with a war that will never end.

411
00:23:43,797 --> 00:23:45,841
The Time War will begin anew.

412
00:23:46,967 --> 00:23:48,302
You know that Doctor.

413
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:52,473
(BEEP)

414
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:54,767
Done.

415
00:24:02,358 --> 00:24:05,277
No... Don't you dare, no, no!

416
00:24:05,361 --> 00:24:06,528
(WHOOSHING)

417
00:24:06,862 --> 00:24:09,073
They're asking for my help!

418
00:24:09,198 --> 00:24:13,077
And if you give it
war will be the consequence.

419
00:24:13,202 --> 00:24:17,831
I will not let that happen at any cost.

420
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:25,047
Speak your name
and this world will burn!

421
00:24:25,214 --> 00:24:27,549
No, this planet is protected.

422
00:24:27,841 --> 00:24:29,259
(BELL TOLLS)

423
00:24:35,724 --> 00:24:38,352
DOCTOR: So, you lot, quick word,
thank you.

424
00:24:38,936 --> 00:24:42,564
Spot of news,
Christmas has a new sheriff.

425
00:24:43,565 --> 00:24:46,902
Hello, everyone, I'm the Doctor.

426
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:53,867
Attention.

427
00:24:54,410 --> 00:24:58,580
Attention all Chapels and Choirs
of the Papal Mainframe.

428
00:24:59,581 --> 00:25:03,627
The siege of Trenzalore is now begun.

429
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:10,259
There will now be
an unscheduled faith change.

430
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:16,598
From this moment on,
I dedicate this church to one cause.

431
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:19,268
Silence.

432
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:25,941
The Doctor will not speak his name
and war will not begin.

433
00:25:27,443 --> 00:25:30,738
Silence will fall!

434
00:25:31,155 --> 00:25:33,449
ALL: Silence will fall.

435
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:35,617
ALL: Silence will fall.

436
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:38,495
TASHA LEM: In the time that followed,

437
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:41,457
the Papal Mainframe
strove to maintain the peace

438
00:25:41,582 --> 00:25:43,917
between the Doctor and his enemies.

439
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:47,755
SONTARAN 1: We remain undetectable
to the Papal Mainframe.

440
00:25:49,965 --> 00:25:52,176
Commander Skarr!
That's the detection warning.

441
00:25:52,301 --> 00:25:53,343
(SONIC BEEPING)

442
00:25:53,469 --> 00:25:55,637
Our invisibility cloak is compromised.

443
00:25:56,346 --> 00:25:59,808
-What's wrong with it?
-I don't know, I can't see it.

444
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:02,227
Well, it looks invisible to me.

445
00:26:02,311 --> 00:26:03,353
(THUD)

446
00:26:05,856 --> 00:26:07,566
ETHEREAL VOICE:
The Church of the Papal Mainframe

447
00:26:07,649 --> 00:26:09,109
apologizes for your death.

448
00:26:09,193 --> 00:26:11,111
The relevant afterlives
have been notified.

449
00:26:12,863 --> 00:26:15,491
TASHA LEM: As the days passed,
and the years,

450
00:26:15,616 --> 00:26:18,327
the Doctor stayed true to his word.

451
00:26:18,994 --> 00:26:20,704
On the fields of Trenzalore,

452
00:26:20,829 --> 00:26:25,626
he stood as protector, both
of his own people and his new home.

453
00:26:28,128 --> 00:26:31,840
Over time, the Doctor's enemies
would find new,

454
00:26:32,174 --> 00:26:35,719
stranger ways to enter
the town called Christmas.

455
00:26:38,347 --> 00:26:39,973
Are you there?

456
00:26:40,849 --> 00:26:41,892
Hello?

457
00:26:44,061 --> 00:26:45,479
Am I getting warm?

458
00:26:59,576 --> 00:27:01,036
There's another one!

459
00:27:04,706 --> 00:27:06,208
There's another one!

460
00:27:07,876 --> 00:27:09,837
There's another one!

461
00:27:11,088 --> 00:27:12,339
There's another one!

462
00:27:12,673 --> 00:27:16,510
Doctor! Doctor! There's another one.

463
00:27:22,266 --> 00:27:23,934
WOODEN CYBERMAN: Incinerate.

464
00:27:33,110 --> 00:27:36,196
The Doctor is required.

465
00:27:42,369 --> 00:27:43,537
-There you go, Barnable.
-Thanks.

466
00:27:43,620 --> 00:27:46,874
Working fine, nice action.
Don't leave it out in the rain again.

467
00:27:47,791 --> 00:27:49,501
Fixed the wheels and the anti-grave.

468
00:27:49,585 --> 00:27:51,378
-The anti-what's?
-Yeah, might have gone a bit far.

469
00:27:51,461 --> 00:27:55,424
Now, then, what do we have today?
Don't you move one step further.

470
00:27:55,799 --> 00:27:59,178
Wooden Cyberman. Nice, like it.

471
00:27:59,261 --> 00:28:02,306
Low-tech, doesn't set off
the alarms upstairs.

472
00:28:04,725 --> 00:28:05,767
(CREAKING)

473
00:28:17,571 --> 00:28:19,865
Only bit of tech allowed in,
got in before the truce.

474
00:28:19,948 --> 00:28:22,367
Now, I just sent an instruction
to your firearm

475
00:28:22,451 --> 00:28:24,953
to reverse the polarity
and fire out the back end.

476
00:28:25,078 --> 00:28:30,209
Now, as we're standing in a truth field,
you'll understand I cannot be lying.

477
00:28:30,292 --> 00:28:33,754
If you like,
you can scan my screwdriver,

478
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:35,923
verify that's the signal I sent.

479
00:28:37,799 --> 00:28:40,093
Signal verified.

480
00:28:44,473 --> 00:28:47,809
Yes, I probably should have mentioned,
this doesn't work on wood!

481
00:28:49,478 --> 00:28:52,481
You send your friends up there
a message from the Doctor.

482
00:28:53,190 --> 00:28:56,026
You tell them the Doctor stays.

483
00:29:01,949 --> 00:29:02,991
Next.

484
00:29:04,534 --> 00:29:05,827
(FIREWORKS BURSTING)

485
00:29:06,495 --> 00:29:09,706
TASHA LEM: With every victory,
the town celebrated.

486
00:29:09,831 --> 00:29:12,376
And there's me arm-wrestling
a Draconian...

487
00:29:12,501 --> 00:29:16,463
In time, the Doctor seemed to forget
he'd lived any other life.

488
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:19,007
DOCTOR: Christmas is defended!

489
00:29:19,716 --> 00:29:24,513
And the people of the town came to love
the man who stayed for Christmas.

490
00:29:26,682 --> 00:29:30,018
If you want to be the drunk giraffe,
you've got to commit!

491
00:29:30,310 --> 00:29:34,481
Don't be cool, guys. Cool is not cool.

492
00:29:34,564 --> 00:29:36,525
ALL: Cool is not cool!

493
00:29:36,650 --> 00:29:38,193
And what's the dance we're doing?

494
00:29:38,318 --> 00:29:40,195
ALL: The drunk giraffe!

495
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:43,073
The drunk giraffe, yes! Merry Christmas!

496
00:29:43,198 --> 00:29:45,033
Give me a hug, bring it in.

497
00:29:45,158 --> 00:29:47,244
(ALL CHEERING)

498
00:29:50,038 --> 00:29:51,707
How's your father's barn?

499
00:29:51,832 --> 00:29:55,085
You've fixed the leak all right but
he say it's bigger on the inside now.

500
00:29:55,210 --> 00:29:58,046
Shhh! They'll all want one!

501
00:30:01,049 --> 00:30:02,259
(WHOOSHING)

502
00:30:03,343 --> 00:30:06,096
BARNABLE: What is it? What's that noise?

503
00:30:06,722 --> 00:30:10,851
Well, where have you been
for 300 years?

504
00:30:12,352 --> 00:30:14,104
-BARNABLE: What's that?
-It's my ship.

505
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:15,647
-Your what?
-It's my Tardis.

506
00:30:15,731 --> 00:30:17,441
That's how I got here
in the first place.

507
00:30:20,694 --> 00:30:23,030
Does this mean you're leaving?

508
00:30:26,408 --> 00:30:28,201
(ALL MURMURING)

509
00:30:53,769 --> 00:30:55,145
(CLARA GASPS)

510
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:00,317
What are you doing here?

511
00:31:06,782 --> 00:31:09,826
-I was in space.
-Well, you were in the time vortex.

512
00:31:09,951 --> 00:31:11,703
She must have extended the force field.

513
00:31:11,787 --> 00:31:16,750
No wonder! No wonder she's late,
dragging you around.

514
00:31:19,628 --> 00:31:20,921
You tricked me.

515
00:31:21,129 --> 00:31:22,506
I saved you!

516
00:31:22,756 --> 00:31:24,132
You didn't even say goodbye!

517
00:31:24,257 --> 00:31:26,301
I am furious with you!

518
00:31:26,468 --> 00:31:28,970
Well, I am not even talking to you!

519
00:31:29,930 --> 00:31:31,640
(LAUGHING)

520
00:31:32,974 --> 00:31:34,017
(GROANS)

521
00:31:37,312 --> 00:31:38,688
(CHUCKLES)

522
00:31:49,991 --> 00:31:54,663
Ah, Doctor, fixing toys
and fighting monsters.

523
00:31:56,498 --> 00:31:58,458
The turkey isn't done yet.

524
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:02,879
Is it still asking the question?

525
00:32:03,004 --> 00:32:06,341
Oh, it never stops.
Come upstairs, it's almost time.

526
00:32:06,508 --> 00:32:07,843
-What for?
-Dawn.

527
00:32:09,177 --> 00:32:12,222
The light here lasts only a few minutes.
You don't want to miss it.

528
00:32:15,183 --> 00:32:17,352
Well, it's a standoff.

529
00:32:17,853 --> 00:32:20,647
They can't attack in case
I unleash the Time Lords

530
00:32:20,730 --> 00:32:26,903
and I can't run away because they'll
burn this planet to stop the Time Lords.

531
00:32:27,070 --> 00:32:29,281
Hey, after all these years,
I've finally found somewhere

532
00:32:29,364 --> 00:32:31,199
that needs me to stick around.

533
00:32:33,493 --> 00:32:36,496
A town called Christmas.
Could've been worse.

534
00:32:37,414 --> 00:32:40,876
Right, there you go, buddy. Comfy?

535
00:32:41,001 --> 00:32:42,043
(BEEPING)

536
00:32:42,169 --> 00:32:43,587
Comfort is irrelevant.

537
00:32:44,212 --> 00:32:45,589
How's that, is that better?

538
00:32:45,922 --> 00:32:47,382
Affirmative.

539
00:32:48,216 --> 00:32:49,843
You just take it easy, buddy.

540
00:32:53,555 --> 00:32:54,598
He's getting old.

541
00:32:56,850 --> 00:33:01,396
I do my best for him but
I just can't get the parts, you know.

542
00:33:01,563 --> 00:33:04,566
Hey. Know the feeling.

543
00:33:04,691 --> 00:33:05,734
Where'd you get these?

544
00:33:05,859 --> 00:33:08,778
I have a supplier,
the pinks ones are best.

545
00:33:11,031 --> 00:33:13,241
CYBERHEAD: I have developed a fault.

546
00:33:13,783 --> 00:33:16,912
Hey, don't you worry, Handles.
You're just dreaming.

547
00:33:17,078 --> 00:33:20,749
The sun's coming up very soon,
you just hang on in there.

548
00:33:20,957 --> 00:33:26,421
I have developed a fault.
I have developed a fault.

549
00:33:26,796 --> 00:33:31,218
Hey, Handles. Come on. Come on.

550
00:33:31,635 --> 00:33:33,595
One more dawn, you can do it.

551
00:33:34,262 --> 00:33:36,973
You've got it in you, come on,
just hang on in there.

552
00:33:37,098 --> 00:33:39,976
Attention! Emergency! Attention!

553
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:41,895
Handles? What is it, what's wrong?

554
00:33:42,270 --> 00:33:44,189
Urgent action required!

555
00:33:44,272 --> 00:33:49,444
You must patch the telephone device
back through the console unit.

556
00:34:06,294 --> 00:34:08,505
Come back. Handles?

557
00:34:11,841 --> 00:34:12,926
Handles?

558
00:34:18,473 --> 00:34:19,516
(SIGHS)

559
00:34:25,981 --> 00:34:28,400
Thank you, Handles.

560
00:34:28,483 --> 00:34:31,695
And well done. Well done, mate.

561
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:39,160
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

562
00:34:45,834 --> 00:34:47,794
What do you think of my new place?

563
00:34:48,003 --> 00:34:50,297
Come up here once a day
for a few minutes

564
00:34:51,006 --> 00:34:53,675
to remind myself of what it is
I'm protecting.

565
00:34:54,634 --> 00:34:55,885
It's beautiful.

566
00:34:57,470 --> 00:34:59,347
Why did you send me away?

567
00:35:02,058 --> 00:35:06,438
Because if I hadn't,
I'd have buried you a long time ago.

568
00:35:06,521 --> 00:35:08,023
No, you wouldn't.

569
00:35:08,398 --> 00:35:09,858
I would never have
let you get stuck here.

570
00:35:09,983 --> 00:35:15,030
Ha! Everyone gets stuck somewhere
eventually, Clara.

571
00:35:16,156 --> 00:35:18,325
-Everything ends.
-Except you.

572
00:35:21,077 --> 00:35:23,246
Have you been paying attention?

573
00:35:23,872 --> 00:35:24,998
I'm an old man now.

574
00:35:25,373 --> 00:35:29,794
But you don't die. You change.
You pop right back up with a new face.

575
00:35:29,878 --> 00:35:31,671
No, not forever.

576
00:35:32,005 --> 00:35:37,552
I can change 12 times,
13 versions of me, 13 silly Doctors.

577
00:35:37,677 --> 00:35:39,220
Okay, so you're number 11, so?

578
00:35:39,387 --> 00:35:43,224
Ha! Are we forgetting
Captain Grumpy, huh?

579
00:35:43,391 --> 00:35:45,560
I didn't call myself the Doctor
during the Time War

580
00:35:45,685 --> 00:35:47,729
but it was still a regeneration.

581
00:35:47,854 --> 00:35:49,022
Okay, so you're number 12.

582
00:35:49,105 --> 00:35:51,608
Number 10 once regenerated
and kept the same face.

583
00:35:51,733 --> 00:35:53,401
I had vanity issues at the time.

584
00:35:53,610 --> 00:35:56,404
Twelve regenerations, Clara.

585
00:35:56,696 --> 00:35:59,574
I can't ever do it again.
This is where I end up.

586
00:36:01,951 --> 00:36:05,413
This face, this version of me.

587
00:36:08,917 --> 00:36:11,086
We saw this planet in the future,
remember?

588
00:36:12,295 --> 00:36:14,047
All those graves,

589
00:36:15,048 --> 00:36:16,800
one of them mine.

590
00:36:20,470 --> 00:36:22,055
-Change the future.
-I can't.

591
00:36:22,138 --> 00:36:23,723
-You've got your Tardis back.
-Ha!

592
00:36:23,807 --> 00:36:26,309
You think I'm just going to fly away,
abandon everyone?

593
00:36:26,726 --> 00:36:28,103
Of course not.

594
00:36:28,978 --> 00:36:31,398
But you've been protecting
this town for over 300 years,

595
00:36:31,481 --> 00:36:32,774
do you not think
it's anybody else's go yet?

596
00:36:32,899 --> 00:36:34,442
There is no one else to protect it.

597
00:36:34,734 --> 00:36:36,152
(SIGHS) There's not going
to be you forever.

598
00:36:36,277 --> 00:36:37,445
It's going to end the same way
whatever you do.

599
00:36:37,612 --> 00:36:40,907
Every life I save is a victory.
Every single one.

600
00:36:41,616 --> 00:36:43,451
What about your life?

601
00:36:44,953 --> 00:36:46,871
Just for once, after all of this time,

602
00:36:46,955 --> 00:36:49,582
have you not earned
the right to think about that?

603
00:36:53,962 --> 00:36:55,338
(SIGHS) Sorry.

604
00:36:56,506 --> 00:37:00,135
Wrong thing to say.
We shouldn't be having an argument.

605
00:37:00,343 --> 00:37:04,973
Clara, I've been having that argument
for the last 300 years, all by myself.

606
00:37:05,098 --> 00:37:06,391
But you didn't have your Tardis.

607
00:37:06,474 --> 00:37:09,477
Ah, yes, well,
that made it easier to stay.

608
00:37:11,855 --> 00:37:12,939
True.

609
00:37:15,859 --> 00:37:17,444
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

610
00:37:17,527 --> 00:37:18,820
TASHA LEM: Doctor!

611
00:37:18,987 --> 00:37:22,991
Ah, look who's woken up!

612
00:37:23,533 --> 00:37:26,619
The Church of the Silence
requests parlay.

613
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:29,706
Your rights and safety are sanctified.

614
00:37:29,831 --> 00:37:31,166
I'll be right up.

615
00:37:31,624 --> 00:37:32,959
I'm sending a transporter.

616
00:37:33,126 --> 00:37:36,379
Nah, don't bother.
I've got me motor back.

617
00:37:37,964 --> 00:37:39,340
It's gone dark.

618
00:37:40,008 --> 00:37:42,051
Yeah, well, the sun's gone down.

619
00:37:42,177 --> 00:37:43,178
Already?

620
00:37:44,846 --> 00:37:46,723
Everything ends, Clara.

621
00:37:47,891 --> 00:37:50,018
And sooner than you think.

622
00:37:52,687 --> 00:37:55,064
(CHILDREN CLAMORING)

623
00:38:03,072 --> 00:38:04,157
Hmm.

624
00:38:09,037 --> 00:38:10,914
Are you guarding my Tardis, Barnable?

625
00:38:11,539 --> 00:38:12,874
Are you coming back?

626
00:38:13,374 --> 00:38:17,253
Ah, come on. You know me.

627
00:38:18,046 --> 00:38:19,088
I'LL wait.

628
00:38:30,016 --> 00:38:33,394
CLARA: She hasn't aged much.
DOCTOR: No, she's against aging.

629
00:38:33,728 --> 00:38:35,063
Approach.

630
00:38:37,565 --> 00:38:40,068
Confess!/

631
00:38:41,194 --> 00:38:42,362
What are those things?

632
00:38:42,445 --> 00:38:44,239
-Confess!
-DOCTOR: Confessional Priests.

633
00:38:44,906 --> 00:38:50,370
Very popular, genetically engineered so
you forget everything you told them.

634
00:38:50,537 --> 00:38:52,247
-Told who?
-There you go.

635
00:38:58,378 --> 00:39:00,463
-(DOCTOR SNIFFS)
-TASHA LEM: Satisfactory?

636
00:39:01,089 --> 00:39:02,590
Where are the pink ones?

637
00:39:03,091 --> 00:39:06,261
E-numbers.
You're hyper enough as it is.

638
00:39:06,553 --> 00:39:10,598
So this is sweet. Middle of a siege
and you two have little chats?

639
00:39:10,807 --> 00:39:13,977
She's right.
This situation cannot continue.

640
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:16,145
It can't end, either.

641
00:39:16,646 --> 00:39:17,730
DALEK: Report.

642
00:39:20,233 --> 00:39:22,777
The Time Lord has entered the trap.

643
00:39:28,783 --> 00:39:30,785
Why did you ever come to Trenzalore?

644
00:39:31,995 --> 00:39:35,498
Well, I did come to Trenzalore
and nothing can change that now.

645
00:39:35,623 --> 00:39:37,417
Didn't stop you trying, though, did it?

646
00:39:37,500 --> 00:39:41,421
Not me. The Kovarian Chapter broke away.

647
00:39:41,504 --> 00:39:43,298
They traveled back along your timeline

648
00:39:43,423 --> 00:39:45,925
and tried to prevent
you ever reaching Trenzalore.

649
00:39:46,301 --> 00:39:47,969
So that's who blew up my Tardis.

650
00:39:49,762 --> 00:39:51,139
I thought I'd left the bath running.

651
00:39:51,347 --> 00:39:55,435
They blew up your time capsule,
created the very cracks in the universe

652
00:39:55,518 --> 00:39:57,478
through which the Time Lords
are now calling.

653
00:39:57,645 --> 00:39:59,606
The destiny trap.

654
00:39:59,689 --> 00:40:02,442
You can't change history
if you're part of it.

655
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:04,360
They engineered
a psychopath to kill you.

656
00:40:04,485 --> 00:40:06,613
Totally married her.

657
00:40:06,696 --> 00:40:09,532
I'd never have made it here
alive without River Song.

658
00:40:10,366 --> 00:40:13,411
I'm not interested in
changing history, Doctor.

659
00:40:13,494 --> 00:40:15,663
I want to change the future.

660
00:40:15,788 --> 00:40:18,708
The Daleks send for
reinforcements daily,

661
00:40:18,833 --> 00:40:20,668
they are massing for war.

662
00:40:21,044 --> 00:40:24,505
Three days ago, they attacked
the Mainframe itself.

663
00:40:24,672 --> 00:40:27,008
-They attacked here?
-How did you stop them?

664
00:40:27,467 --> 00:40:28,676
Stop them?

665
00:40:29,302 --> 00:40:30,345
It was slaughter.

666
00:40:30,511 --> 00:40:32,680
Why didn't you call me?
I could have helped.

667
00:40:33,348 --> 00:40:34,349
I tried.

668
00:40:35,183 --> 00:40:38,019
I died in this room,
screaming your name.

669
00:40:39,896 --> 00:40:40,980
(WHISPERING) No.

670
00:40:41,522 --> 00:40:44,150
Oh, I died.

671
00:40:47,695 --> 00:40:50,573
It's funny the things
that slip your mind.

672
00:40:50,698 --> 00:40:51,699
(GRUNTS)

673
00:40:52,492 --> 00:40:55,203
No! No, no, no, Tasha, no, please!

674
00:40:55,328 --> 00:40:56,663
No, Tasha, no! Fight it.

675
00:40:58,665 --> 00:41:00,208
Tash, fight it!

676
00:41:02,043 --> 00:41:06,506
Step away from the Dalek unit, Doctor.

677
00:41:08,091 --> 00:41:09,634
You shouldn't even know who I am.

678
00:41:09,717 --> 00:41:16,724
Information concerning the Doctor was
harvested from the cadaver of Tasha Lem.

679
00:41:18,726 --> 00:41:21,437
Bet she never told you how to break
the Trenzalore force-field, though.

680
00:41:21,562 --> 00:41:22,605
She'd have died first.

681
00:41:22,855 --> 00:41:24,732
Several times.

682
00:41:25,066 --> 00:41:28,695
Well, you'd better kill me, then, go on.
But before you do...

683
00:41:28,903 --> 00:41:34,367
THE GENERAL: Doctor who?
Doctor who? Doctor who?

684
00:41:34,450 --> 00:41:38,705
I'm a tough old bird,
I'll be ages dying.

685
00:41:38,788 --> 00:41:43,960
Way enough time to answer a question.
And oh dear, what happens then, boys?

686
00:41:44,585 --> 00:41:48,256
-DALEK: You will die in silence, Doctor.
-(GASPS)

687
00:41:48,423 --> 00:41:51,259
Or your associate will die.

688
00:41:53,261 --> 00:41:56,139
Fine, go on. Kill her. Kill her!

689
00:41:56,389 --> 00:42:00,268
See if I care. But tell me,
what are you going to do next?

690
00:42:00,435 --> 00:42:04,105
See how the Time Lord betrays?

691
00:42:04,605 --> 00:42:08,484
You'll kill me anyway,
what difference does it make?

692
00:42:08,609 --> 00:42:10,862
I'm not afraid. I leave that to you.

693
00:42:10,945 --> 00:42:12,822
You see, Tasha,
that's what I'm talking about!

694
00:42:12,947 --> 00:42:16,284
That is a woman!

695
00:42:16,784 --> 00:42:19,037
I always knew you were a bit spineless,

696
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:23,458
you and your pointless church.
Why did I ever rely on you?

697
00:42:23,583 --> 00:42:26,627
Never trust a nun to do a Doctor's work.

698
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:28,671
(GRUNTS)

699
00:42:30,256 --> 00:42:32,467
(EXPLOSIONS)

700
00:42:33,134 --> 00:42:35,303
And she's back!

701
00:42:37,972 --> 00:42:39,265
You never could resist a row.

702
00:42:39,348 --> 00:42:42,226
-Kiss me when I ask!
-Well, you'd better ask nicely.

703
00:42:42,310 --> 00:42:43,686
In your dreams!

704
00:42:43,811 --> 00:42:45,897
Right, get us back to the Tardis,
can you do that?

705
00:42:45,980 --> 00:42:48,816
Yep, but quickly,
the Dalek inside me is waking.

706
00:42:49,275 --> 00:42:50,526
-Fight it.
-I can't.

707
00:42:50,818 --> 00:42:51,986
Listen to me,

708
00:42:52,111 --> 00:42:54,864
you have been fighting the psychopath
inside you all your life,

709
00:42:54,989 --> 00:42:58,326
shut up and win!
That is an order, Tasha Lem.

710
00:42:58,493 --> 00:43:01,412
The force-field will hold for a while
but it will decay

711
00:43:01,496 --> 00:43:03,122
and there are breaches already.

712
00:43:03,289 --> 00:43:05,500
Then this isn't a siege anymore,
it's a war.

713
00:43:05,666 --> 00:43:08,377
It's all up to you now,
fight the Daleks, inside and out.

714
00:43:08,503 --> 00:43:09,587
You can do it, I know you can.

715
00:43:09,670 --> 00:43:10,838
Oh, I see.

716
00:43:11,672 --> 00:43:13,800
You've got your Tardis back,
haven't you?

717
00:43:13,966 --> 00:43:15,301
Time to fly away.

718
00:43:15,384 --> 00:43:19,347
Tasha, please, please.

719
00:43:20,181 --> 00:43:21,182
Thank you.

720
00:43:21,349 --> 00:43:27,063
None of this was for you, you
fatuous egotist, it was for the peace.

721
00:43:29,315 --> 00:43:30,483
Fly away, Doctor!

722
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:35,738
(WHOOSHING)

723
00:43:36,906 --> 00:43:37,990
(TIMER DINGS)

724
00:43:38,074 --> 00:43:39,700
-It's done.
-What is?

725
00:43:40,368 --> 00:43:41,828
Your turkey.

726
00:43:42,036 --> 00:43:43,371
Either that or it's woken up.

727
00:43:43,538 --> 00:43:45,665
-(LAUGHS) You want some?
-Go on, then!

728
00:43:45,748 --> 00:43:46,874
Got any plates?

729
00:43:46,999 --> 00:43:49,085
Do you know,
I've even got Christmas crackers.

730
00:43:55,758 --> 00:43:57,176
One thing.

731
00:43:58,761 --> 00:44:01,222
Give me those big sad eyes,
look at me so I know you're not lying

732
00:44:01,347 --> 00:44:03,558
and tell me you will never
send me away ever again.

733
00:44:06,394 --> 00:44:08,187
Clara Oswald,

734
00:44:10,273 --> 00:44:14,068
I will never send you away again.

735
00:44:21,951 --> 00:44:23,369
CLARA: Turkey smells good!

736
00:44:24,370 --> 00:44:26,080
DOCTOR: Yep, smells great.

737
00:44:31,127 --> 00:44:32,211
CLARA: It's perfect.

738
00:44:37,049 --> 00:44:38,801
Merry Christmas.

739
00:44:43,598 --> 00:44:44,599
Doctor?

740
00:44:50,897 --> 00:44:52,273
(TARDIS DOOR CLOSES)

741
00:45:01,616 --> 00:45:03,159
(WHOOSHING)

742
00:45:10,291 --> 00:45:12,460
If you're not leaving,
why did you bring it back?

743
00:45:13,961 --> 00:45:15,421
It's a reminder.

744
00:45:20,968 --> 00:45:25,765
Besides, I might leave tomorrow
or the next day.

745
00:45:27,808 --> 00:45:29,685
Or the day after that.

746
00:45:38,152 --> 00:45:40,821
TASHA LEM: And so,
to the fields of Trenzalore

747
00:45:40,947 --> 00:45:43,199
came all the Time Lord's enemies.

748
00:45:44,951 --> 00:45:48,663
For this was the winter of the Doctor.

749
00:45:53,834 --> 00:45:58,756
In time, when all other races
had retreated or burned,

750
00:45:58,839 --> 00:46:03,094
only the Church of the Mainframe
remained in the path of the Daleks.

751
00:46:03,177 --> 00:46:04,220
(GROANS)

752
00:46:04,971 --> 00:46:09,225
And so those ancient enemies,
the Doctor and the Silence,

753
00:46:09,350 --> 00:46:13,854
stood back-to-back on
the fields of Trenzalore.

754
00:46:16,482 --> 00:46:19,986
Merry Christmas, everyone!
Merry Christmas, everyone!

755
00:46:20,069 --> 00:46:22,655
LINDA: Other fish in the sea,
that's what I'm saying.

756
00:46:22,738 --> 00:46:25,491
Linda, I don't think Clara
wants to talk about it.

757
00:46:25,700 --> 00:46:29,370
I've got a suggestion, that's all.
I've got a list of suggestions.

758
00:46:29,537 --> 00:46:30,579
Linda!

759
00:46:30,705 --> 00:46:32,832
You could make
a boy band out of my list!

760
00:46:32,915 --> 00:46:36,127
-I hate boy bands.
-Of course you don't, not at your age.

761
00:46:36,210 --> 00:46:38,045
These crackers are rubbish.

762
00:46:38,671 --> 00:46:40,589
-LINDA: I bought them.
-I know.

763
00:46:41,215 --> 00:46:42,216
LINDA: They're classy.

764
00:46:42,425 --> 00:46:43,551
They don't have jokes.

765
00:46:43,676 --> 00:46:44,844
Exactly.

766
00:46:44,927 --> 00:46:46,387
They've got poems.

767
00:46:46,512 --> 00:46:48,055
They're more dramatic crackers.

768
00:46:48,889 --> 00:46:50,558
I like the jokes.

769
00:46:51,851 --> 00:46:53,602
Tell us a joke, Gran.

770
00:46:53,728 --> 00:46:54,729
You know loads of jokes.

771
00:46:54,895 --> 00:46:56,689
I think we're probably
talking about my list now.

772
00:46:56,856 --> 00:46:58,316
Probably not.

773
00:46:58,399 --> 00:47:01,360
Tell us how you met Dad.
The thing about the pigeon.

774
00:47:01,569 --> 00:47:04,447
I saw him on a pier, on a rainy day.

775
00:47:04,864 --> 00:47:07,450
No, no. Not that one,
the one about the pigeon.

776
00:47:07,908 --> 00:47:09,910
I'd seen him before, lots of times.

777
00:47:10,119 --> 00:47:12,913
But he just looked
so beautiful standing there.

778
00:47:13,122 --> 00:47:15,916
The pigeon in the restaurant,
you remember?

779
00:47:16,042 --> 00:47:19,211
I wanted everything to stop.

780
00:47:19,295 --> 00:47:22,465
I wanted nothing to change ever again.

781
00:47:22,965 --> 00:47:27,595
If he could just keep standing there,
so beautiful.

782
00:47:33,309 --> 00:47:34,894
Long time ago.

783
00:47:39,648 --> 00:47:42,443
Don't hug me so tight, dear,
you'll break something.

784
00:47:42,610 --> 00:47:45,237
-(SOBBING)
-On that's nice, crying at Christmas.

785
00:47:45,446 --> 00:47:46,447
Sorry.

786
00:47:48,282 --> 00:47:49,909
I hope you made a wish.

787
00:47:55,456 --> 00:47:56,916
(WHOOSHING)

788
00:47:57,458 --> 00:47:59,627
Clara? What's wrong, Clara?

789
00:48:07,259 --> 00:48:09,470
Everybody just stay put!

790
00:48:21,357 --> 00:48:22,817
(PANTING)

791
00:48:26,862 --> 00:48:28,155
You can fly the Tardis?

792
00:48:28,364 --> 00:48:30,908
Flying the Tardis was always easy.

793
00:48:30,991 --> 00:48:33,536
It was flying the Doctor
I never quite mastered.

794
00:48:34,453 --> 00:48:35,538
What's happened to him?

795
00:48:39,625 --> 00:48:41,710
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

796
00:48:50,052 --> 00:48:51,345
What am I supposed to do?

797
00:48:51,887 --> 00:48:53,389
He shouldn't die alone.

798
00:48:54,014 --> 00:48:55,224
Go to him.

799
00:49:07,194 --> 00:49:08,737
(EXPLOSION)

800
00:49:33,053 --> 00:49:34,722
DOCTOR: Barnable?

801
00:49:38,017 --> 00:49:39,727
Clara.

802
00:49:47,193 --> 00:49:48,235
Hello, Doctor.

803
00:49:53,782 --> 00:49:55,367
Were you always so young?

804
00:49:56,577 --> 00:49:58,787
Nah. That was you.

805
00:50:05,544 --> 00:50:06,587
Huh.

806
00:50:15,095 --> 00:50:17,389
Seek the Doctor.

807
00:50:17,640 --> 00:50:19,934
-Merry Christmas.
-Merry Christmas.

808
00:50:20,559 --> 00:50:21,602
(CHUCKLES)

809
00:50:25,940 --> 00:50:29,610
Hey, it's okay. It's fine. Don't worry.

810
00:50:30,945 --> 00:50:31,987
Ah!

811
00:50:34,448 --> 00:50:36,951
Is there a joke, huh?

812
00:50:40,287 --> 00:50:43,666
Extract from Thoughts On A Clock
by Eric Ritchie junior.

813
00:50:44,250 --> 00:50:46,585
Is it a knock-knock one?
Those are the best.

814
00:50:47,294 --> 00:50:48,587
I don't think so.

815
00:50:48,671 --> 00:50:49,964
Well, read it. Go on.

816
00:50:51,799 --> 00:50:57,388
"And now it's time for one last bow
Like all your other selves

817
00:50:57,471 --> 00:51:02,309
"Eleven's hour is over now
The clock is striking twelve's."

818
00:51:03,978 --> 00:51:05,354
I don't get it.

819
00:51:05,479 --> 00:51:09,525
DALEK: Doctor!
The Doctor will be brought!

820
00:51:09,650 --> 00:51:13,112
The Daleks demand the Doctor.

821
00:51:15,155 --> 00:51:19,618
They're here. The Daleks,
we can't stop them. They want you.

822
00:51:20,286 --> 00:51:23,831
All right, Barnable. Are you Barnable?

823
00:51:24,373 --> 00:51:25,666
No, Doctor.

824
00:51:25,874 --> 00:51:30,170
It's okay, Barnable, don't worry.
I have got a plan.

825
00:51:31,005 --> 00:51:32,506
Off you pop.

826
00:51:35,676 --> 00:51:37,344
(EXPLOSION)

827
00:51:38,470 --> 00:51:41,473
I haven't got a plan
but people love it when I say that.

828
00:51:41,724 --> 00:51:42,808
Doctor, what are you going to do?

829
00:51:42,975 --> 00:51:44,810
I don't know. (GROANING)

830
00:51:44,893 --> 00:51:48,856
Talk very fast,
hope something good happens,

831
00:51:48,981 --> 00:51:50,482
take the credit.

832
00:51:50,566 --> 00:51:51,900
That's generally how it works.

833
00:51:52,026 --> 00:51:56,697
-Doctor...
-Not this time, though. This is it.

834
00:51:57,698 --> 00:51:59,199
-No!
-Yes.

835
00:52:00,826 --> 00:52:04,580
We saw the future, Clara.
This is how it ends.

836
00:52:04,705 --> 00:52:05,956
-Change it!
-Ha!

837
00:52:06,040 --> 00:52:08,292
Like Tasha said, change the future!

838
00:52:08,375 --> 00:52:12,379
I could have once,
when there were Time Lords.

839
00:52:12,504 --> 00:52:14,006
Not anymore.

840
00:52:14,590 --> 00:52:17,217
Locate the Doctor.

841
00:52:18,218 --> 00:52:20,846
No, you're going to stay here.

842
00:52:20,929 --> 00:52:22,348
Promise me you will.

843
00:52:22,431 --> 00:52:25,684
-Why?
-I'll be keeping you safe.

844
00:52:28,187 --> 00:52:33,359
One last victory. Allow me that.
Give me that,

845
00:52:36,570 --> 00:52:38,739
my impossible girl.

846
00:52:42,201 --> 00:52:43,702
Thank you

847
00:52:44,870 --> 00:52:46,372
and goodbye.

848
00:53:00,803 --> 00:53:05,099
Trouble with Daleks is
they take so long to say anything.

849
00:53:05,766 --> 00:53:08,936
Probably die of boredom
before they shoot me.

850
00:53:12,147 --> 00:53:15,401
The Doctor is required.

851
00:53:21,156 --> 00:53:24,785
Listen to me, you lot. Listen! Help him.

852
00:53:26,412 --> 00:53:30,290
Help him change the future.
Do it. Do something.

853
00:53:34,795 --> 00:53:36,839
DALEK: Doctor!

854
00:53:40,926 --> 00:53:43,512
You've been asking a question

855
00:53:45,139 --> 00:53:48,183
and it's time someone told you,
you've been getting it wrong.

856
00:53:53,355 --> 00:53:54,857
His name...

857
00:53:56,483 --> 00:53:58,944
His name is the Doctor.

858
00:53:59,153 --> 00:54:04,074
All the name he needs.
Everything you need to know about him.

859
00:54:04,158 --> 00:54:06,368
And if you love him,

860
00:54:08,829 --> 00:54:13,709
then you should...help him.

861
00:54:15,961 --> 00:54:17,004
Help him.

862
00:54:24,303 --> 00:54:25,345
(RUMBLING)

863
00:54:40,652 --> 00:54:42,905
Sorry I'm a bit slow.

864
00:54:44,490 --> 00:54:47,034
I may not be at my best right now.

865
00:54:47,201 --> 00:54:50,287
You are dying, Doctor.

866
00:54:50,370 --> 00:54:53,207
Yes, I'm dying.

867
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:58,712
You've been trying to kill me
for centuries and here I am,

868
00:54:59,713 --> 00:55:02,007
dying of old age.

869
00:55:02,883 --> 00:55:05,052
If you want something done,
do it yourself.

870
00:55:05,260 --> 00:55:10,682
You will die and the Time Lords
will never return.

871
00:55:11,058 --> 00:55:13,310
You still can't work up the courage
to shoot me, can you?

872
00:55:13,393 --> 00:55:17,064
You're still worried I've got
something up my sleeve!

873
00:55:19,733 --> 00:55:22,110
Well, you knock yourselves out, boys.

874
00:55:24,905 --> 00:55:26,406
I've got nothing this time.

875
00:55:28,408 --> 00:55:30,118
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

876
00:55:56,603 --> 00:56:00,482
DALEK: You will die now, Doctor.

877
00:56:01,108 --> 00:56:03,777
This is the end of you.

878
00:56:07,781 --> 00:56:10,784
The rules of regeneration are known.

879
00:56:12,119 --> 00:56:15,706
You have expended all your lives.

880
00:56:15,789 --> 00:56:18,625
Sorry, what did you say?

881
00:56:18,750 --> 00:56:21,253
Did you mention the rules?

882
00:56:21,587 --> 00:56:24,423
Now, listen! Bit of advice.

883
00:56:24,506 --> 00:56:26,550
Tell me the truth
if you think you know it.

884
00:56:26,633 --> 00:56:29,761
Lay down the law
if you're feeling brave.

885
00:56:29,845 --> 00:56:33,765
But Daleks never, ever

886
00:56:33,849 --> 00:56:36,894
tell me the rules!

887
00:56:36,977 --> 00:56:40,355
-Emergency! Emergency!
-(CLOCK CHIMING)

888
00:56:40,522 --> 00:56:44,693
The Doctor is regenerating!
The Doctor is regenerating!

889
00:56:44,860 --> 00:56:48,071
Oh, look at this.
Regeneration number 13.

890
00:56:48,155 --> 00:56:51,116
We're breaking some serious
science here, boys.

891
00:56:51,867 --> 00:56:56,580
I tell you what,
it's gonna be a whopper! Ha-ha!

892
00:56:56,663 --> 00:56:59,625
Exterminate! Exterminate the Doctor.

893
00:57:00,208 --> 00:57:03,045
You think you can stop me now, Daleks?

894
00:57:03,170 --> 00:57:05,172
If you want my life...

895
00:57:05,297 --> 00:57:06,340
(LAUGHS)

896
00:57:06,673 --> 00:57:11,011
...come and get it!

897
00:57:17,517 --> 00:57:21,980
Get inside! Get off the street,
get inside, quick, quick!

898
00:57:22,314 --> 00:57:23,732
(BELL TOLLING)

899
00:57:31,823 --> 00:57:33,325
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

900
00:57:33,492 --> 00:57:36,036
Love from Gallifrey, boys!

901
00:58:10,195 --> 00:58:12,572
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

902
00:58:24,584 --> 00:58:25,627
Doctor?

903
00:59:25,979 --> 00:59:27,022
(SIGHS)

904
00:59:27,898 --> 00:59:29,191
Doctor!

905
00:59:29,316 --> 00:59:30,317
Hello.

906
00:59:32,152 --> 00:59:34,738
You're young again, you're okay.

907
00:59:35,655 --> 00:59:37,074
You didn't even change your face.

908
00:59:37,157 --> 00:59:42,579
Ha! It's started. I can't stop it now.
This is just the reset.

909
00:59:43,580 --> 00:59:47,209
Whole new regeneration cycle, oh!

910
00:59:48,335 --> 00:59:50,087
-Mmm!
-(LAUGHING)

911
00:59:51,171 --> 00:59:52,380
Taking a bit longer.

912
00:59:54,174 --> 00:59:55,509
Just breaking it in.

913
00:59:57,844 --> 00:59:58,845
Oh!

914
00:59:59,930 --> 01:00:01,348
Oh!

915
01:00:02,182 --> 01:00:04,017
(GRUNTS)

916
01:00:08,230 --> 01:00:10,357
It all just disappears, doesn't it?

917
01:00:10,440 --> 01:00:12,859
Everything you are, gone in a moment,

918
01:00:12,943 --> 01:00:16,196
like breath on a mirror.

919
01:00:18,031 --> 01:00:19,616
Any moment now

920
01:00:21,034 --> 01:00:22,119
he's a-coming.

921
01:00:22,285 --> 01:00:24,704
-Who's coming?
-The Doctor.

922
01:00:26,039 --> 01:00:28,875
You, you are the Doctor.

923
01:00:28,959 --> 01:00:32,796
Yep, and I always will be.

924
01:00:37,634 --> 01:00:41,721
But times change and so must I.

925
01:00:44,808 --> 01:00:45,892
(GIRL LAUGHS)

926
01:00:48,395 --> 01:00:49,437
Amelia?

927
01:00:51,231 --> 01:00:52,566
Who's Amelia?

928
01:00:54,609 --> 01:00:56,486
The first face this face saw.

929
01:01:04,161 --> 01:01:08,123
We all change. When you think about it,

930
01:01:09,082 --> 01:01:13,003
we are all different people
all through our lives.

931
01:01:13,962 --> 01:01:16,965
And that's okay, that's good,
you gotta keep moving,

932
01:01:17,090 --> 01:01:19,301
so long as you remember

933
01:01:19,426 --> 01:01:21,678
all the people that you used to be.

934
01:01:24,681 --> 01:01:27,684
I will not forget one line of this.

935
01:01:28,768 --> 01:01:31,271
Not one day.

936
01:01:31,354 --> 01:01:32,606
I swear.

937
01:01:33,607 --> 01:01:37,110
I will always remember
when the Doctor was me.

938
01:01:56,046 --> 01:01:58,006
Raggedy man.

939
01:02:04,137 --> 01:02:05,138
Good night.

940
01:02:23,031 --> 01:02:24,532
No! No!

941
01:02:26,034 --> 01:02:27,494
Please don't change.

942
01:02:42,550 --> 01:02:43,593
(GROANS)

943
01:02:44,761 --> 01:02:47,430
Kidneys! I've got new kidneys.

944
01:02:47,931 --> 01:02:50,267
-I don't like the color.
-Of your kidneys?

945
01:02:50,684 --> 01:02:53,353
-What's happening?
-We're probably crashing!

946
01:02:54,771 --> 01:02:56,898
-Into what?
-Stay calm.

947
01:02:58,400 --> 01:02:59,859
Just one question.

948
01:03:01,111 --> 01:03:03,571
Do you happen to know
how to fly this thing?

